    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="233"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/11–1444</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Greek
                        Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Diamantopoulos</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to His Excellency the Ambassador
                    of Greece and, with reference to the Greek Embassy’s note no. 4111, November 14,
                    1944, has the honor to inform the Ambassador that appropriate steps are being
                    taken with a view to the early resumption of remittances to Greece. Until normal
                    commercial means of communications can be reestablished, interim arrangements
                    have been made for the transfer of funds, mainly for philanthropic organizations
                    operating in Greece, through official Departmental channels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-26">January 26,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
